Question 6
 If p and q are two simple propositions, then the proposition formed by combining the two given propositions by using the words if and then i.e. “if p then q” is called_____________ or an implication.

Response: Conditional proposition

Correct : Conditional proposition

Score: 1 out of 1 Yes

